    {
      "id": "e04e339fb4ffe074ce111e3103073cd25ea2ea4d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2016-08-11 19:37:46.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\n(7 comments)\n\nI don't think this patch is correct, since it pushes the fix to the client instead of on the server where it belongs.  Consider the case of a server with ZFS recordsize=16MB and an old client using ocd_brw_size=1MB (e.g. unpatched 2.5.x).  In that case the client would get back ocd_brw_size=16MB and do something bad.\n\nThis also needs a conf-sanity test case which sets the server brw_size=4MB and the client max_pages_per_rpc to some odd value (e.g. 7*128KB and 11*128KB) and ensures that it doesn't trigger the LASSERTF() logic.\n\nI agree that there does need to be a fix for the client to prevent it from hitting the LASSERTF() with an older server, but the first fix should be that the OFD sets ofd_brw_size = max(ONE_MB_BRW_SIZE, os->os_bsize) in ofd_init0().",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
